1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's developed a hard format for his stories.

2
00:00:00,895 --> 00:00:07,184
He has never experimented with his material, his plots and characters, and perhaps even style.

3
00:00:07,214 --> 00:00:13,504
But what I'm trying to do now is to get this client to try some new approaches and some new techniques.

4
00:00:13,775 --> 00:00:19,744
He has ability, and if he'll do some experimenting, I'm sure he'll sell much of what he writes.

5
00:00:19,934 --> 00:00:25,585
But until he does, he'll just go on receiving one rejection slip after another.

6
00:00:26,815 --> 00:00:29,905
The advice of the literary consultant is good.

7
00:00:30,095 --> 00:00:32,065
We must have persistence.

8
00:00:32,175 --> 00:00:36,065
But persistence is only one of the ingredients of victory.

9
00:00:36,415 --> 00:00:46,385
We can try and try and try and try and try again and still fail unless we combine persistence with experimentation.

10
00:00:47,135 --> 00:00:52,385
Edison is credited with being one of America's most persistent scientists.

11
00:00:52,655 --> 00:00:58,704
It's reported that he conducted thousands of experiments before he invented the electric light bulb.

12
00:00:58,735 --> 00:01:02,704
But note, Edison conducted experiments.

13
00:01:02,895 --> 00:01:06,224
He persisted in his goal to develop a light bulb.

14
00:01:06,335 --> 00:01:11,504
but he made that persistence pay off by blending it with experimentation.

15
00:01:12,735 --> 00:01:22,145
Persisting in one way is not a guarantee of victory, but persistence blended with experimentation does guarantee success.

16
00:01:23,214 --> 00:01:27,905
Recently, I noticed an article about the continuous search for oil.

17
00:01:28,095 --> 00:01:33,825
It said that oil companies study the rock formations carefully before they drill a well.

18
00:01:34,095 --> 00:01:41,184
Yet, despite their scientific analysis, seven out of eight wells drilled turn out to be dry holes.

19
00:01:41,775 --> 00:01:48,385
Oil companies are persistent in their search for oil, not by digging one hole to ridiculous depths,

20
00:01:48,415 --> 00:01:54,785
but rather by experimenting with a new well when good judgment says the first well won't produce.

21
00:01:55,534 --> 00:02:01,264
Many ambitious people go through life with admirable persistence and show of ambition,

22
00:02:01,375 --> 00:02:05,905
but they fail to succeed because they don't experiment with new approaches.

23
00:02:06,175 --> 00:02:12,224
Stay with your goal, don't waver an inch from it, but don't beat your head against a wall.

24
00:02:12,255 --> 00:02:15,744
If you aren't getting results, try a new approach.
